      "correct": 0,
      "justification_correct": "Clause 6.1.2 requires organizations to determine criteria for asset significance and risk evaluation. Omitting interdependency documentation prevents comprehensive understanding of business impact, resulting in gaps in risk treatment and control selection per ISO/IEC 27002:2022 foundational principles.",
      "justification_wrong": "Options B, C, and D overstate consequences. While significant, omissions trigger corrective actions, not automatic halts or rejections. Audits allow remediation periods per ISO 19011 guidelines for assessment processes."
    },
    {
      "num": 37,
      "text": "An organization implements ISO 27001:2022 with control 5.1 (Policies for information security) stating that all data classification decisions rest solely with the Chief Information Security Officer (CISO). During lead implementation review, what CRITICAL gap exists regarding ISO/IEC 27002:2022 Clause 5.1?",
      "tag": "Organizational Controls & Governance",
