      ],
      "correct": 2,
      "justification_correct": "ISO/IEC 27002:2022 controls 5.3 and 8.3 require documented procedures for privileged access. Emergency access demands compensating controls: authorization documentation, time constraints, activity logging, and post-event validation per Clause 5.15 (Access control) principles.",
      "justification_wrong": "Option B creates operational impossibility. Option C lacks audit trail and approval formality. Option D creates uncontrolled risk exposure. Emergency procedures must include compensating controls with accountability, not circumvent access governance."
    },
    {
      "num": 39,
      "text": "An organization's ISO 27001:2022 ISMS includes control 6.6 (Segregation of duties) implemented through role-based access control (RBAC). Internal audit discovers that developers retain administrative credentials for production databases to 'troubleshoot issues quickly.' What is the PRIMARY non-conformity?",
      "tag": "Technological Controls - Privileged Access Management",
